This Letter of Offer reflects the updated course duration under the new Training Package that the applicant must complete in
order to attain the SIS40221 Certificate IV in Fitness qualification. This is a Conditional Letter of Offer based on the applicant
passing all Units of Competency for Certificate III in Fitness as it is a pre-requisite for the SIS40221 Certificate IV in Fitness.
ALG follows the national/state Health Orders mandate by the government regarding the vaccination requirement. As the
vaccination requirements may vary between courses and external training venues, this may impact an applicant's ability to
commence and/or complete the course if the applicant is not fully vaccinated. Please visit http://ash.alg.edu.au/for the FAQ.

All fees on the above table are tuition fees unless specified otherwise.
Joining Fee is a non-tuition fee, is non-refundable and is a one-time fee payable for any student who has never studied with ALG.
ALG's tuition fees are subject to increase each calendar year (generally in January). The tuition fees shown above are current as at the time of
issuing this Letter of Offer and are indicative only. The actual tuition fees payable will be by reference to ALG's updated fee schedule at the time the
relevant tuition fee payment is due.
Fee due dates may be subject to change. For the most up to date payment due dates, please refer to the timetable available on our website.
